answerText: "The Lake Isle of Innisfree"[10] "The Lake Isle of Innisfree" was written by this Irish poet who described "a vast image out of Spiritus Mundi" in "The Second Coming."

question: Question: The speaker of this poem hears the lapping of water "in the deep heart's core." For 10 points each: [10] Name this poem in which the speaker desires to build a small cabin "of clay and wattles made" at the title location. It begins, "I will arise and go now."
